Comment: French Defence
French Defence
Not great, but can transpose to the main line of the advance varation.(e4 e6,d4 d5, e5)
It may have been better to play d6, immediately challenging the e5 pawn. Taking on d6 gives black a development advantage after Bxd6 or else the pawn centre will crumble.
Back to the main line.
This allows black to swap off his bad bishop. White's whie squared bishop should find a good home on d3, where it creates some kingside pressure.

White should be aiming for a kingside attack as that is where the black king will most likely castle. A plan involving the moves Kh1,f4, and maybe g4 and bringing the knight to g3 to support the attack. Of course the move played is part of the plan, but the pawn on e5 must be defended. Qe2 should be the played and not Re1 as the rook will support the pawns on the kingside.
Free pawn.
